commit.message:
pm: Fix env.d guessing when no /etc/portage/env

When /etc/portage/env is not a directory (→ does not exist), there
are no valid env values.  Therefore, the function should be returning
an empty set rather than None.  The latter implied an error
and prohibited flaggie from recognizing valid values.

Closes: https://github.com/projg2/flaggie/issues/34
Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

verification.payload:
tree f168f6585f3f3e1933f866d5cf687c7b5f3bd17b
parent 3c60a565ec91ba3e2f526d91656e872e86eac526
author Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org> 1676479409 +0100
committer Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org> 1676479409 +0100

pm: Fix env.d guessing when no /etc/portage/env

When /etc/portage/env is not a directory (→ does not exist), there
are no valid env values.  Therefore, the function should be returning
an empty set rather than None.  The latter implied an error
and prohibited flaggie from recognizing valid values.

Closes: https://github.com/projg2/flaggie/issues/34
Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>
